question.text: The below representation is for the diagnosis of __________ fever?

solution.text:
Salmonella typhi is a pathogenic bacterium that causes typhoid or enteric fever in human beings. Poor sanitation, contaminated water and infected milk are some of the main factors responsible for typhoid.

Diagnosis is made by any blood, bone marrow, or stool cultures and with the Widal test.

Sustained high fever ( 39° to 40°C ), weakness, stomach pain, constipation, headache and loss of appetite are some of the common symptoms of this disease.

Patients should be kept on a liquid diet of orange, barley juice and milk. Orange juice, especially, hastens recovery as it increases energy, promotes body immunity and increases urinary output.
